HB 980 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Zeringue
Abstract: Beginning Jan. 1, 2028, prohibits any person who is not receiving state
supplemental pay from serving on the Fireman's Supplemental Pay Board (board).
Present law establishes the board and provides for its membership, powers, and duties.
Proposed law prohibits any person who does not receive state supplemental pay from serving
on the board.
Effective Jan. 1, 2028.
(Adds R.S. 40:1666.5(C))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Remove provisions increasing membership of the board.
2. Remove provisions regarding filling those new positions.
3. Change effective date from signature of the governor to Jan. 1, 2028.
